			</div><div class="et_pb_column et_pb_column_1_2 et_pb_column_2  et_pb_css_mix_blend_mode_passthrough et-last-child">
				
				
				<div class="et_pb_module et_pb_cta_0 et_hover_enabled et_pb_promo  et_pb_text_align_left et_pb_bg_layout_dark et_pb_no_bg">
				
				
				<div class="et_pb_promo_description"><h2 class="et_pb_module_header">Open Positions</h2><div><p><strong>Grades:</strong> Pre-K – High School<br> <strong>Reports To:</strong>&nbsp;Principal and Assistant Principal<br> <strong>Length of Assignment:</strong>&nbsp;6 – 10 months</p>
<p>Our goal at The Einstein Academy is to provide a safe, nurturing, and supportive environment where children can enjoy learning with other students as well as a variety of planned activities.&nbsp;&nbsp; As a member of our staff, one should be constantly aware of where and what each child is doing and help facilitate a positive environment.</p>
<p><strong>Primary purpose:</strong><br>The internship should provide you with opportunities to observe teaching techniques and methods of experienced teachers; practice and develop various teaching abilities and knowledge; and recognize competencies associated with effective teaching.</p>
<p>Under the guidance of cooperating elementary and high school teachers you should have the opportunity to grow as an individual and as a prospective teacher. It is important to remember that the internship is a part-time responsibility.</p></div></div>
				
			</div>
			</div>
				
				
			</div>
				
				
			</div><div class="et_pb_section et_pb_section_3 et_pb_with_background et_pb_section_parallax et_section_regular">
				
				
				
				
					<div class="et_pb_row et_pb_row_2">
				<div class="et_pb_column et_pb_column_4_4 et_pb_column_3  et_pb_css_mix_blend_mode_passthrough et-last-child">
				
				
				<div class="et_pb_module et_pb_cta_1 et_pb_promo  et_pb_text_align_center et_pb_bg_layout_dark et_pb_no_bg">
				
				
				<div class="et_pb_promo_description"><h2 class="et_pb_module_header">Candidate Expectations</h2></div>
				
			</div>
			</div>
				
				
			</div><div class="et_pb_row et_pb_row_3 et_pb_row_fullwidth et_pb_gutters1">
				<div class="et_pb_column et_pb_column_1_2 et_pb_column_4  et_pb_css_mix_blend_mode_passthrough">
				
				
				<div class="et_pb_module et_pb_text et_pb_text_1  et_pb_text_align_left et_pb_bg_layout_light">
				
				
				<div class="et_pb_text_inner"><p><strong>Responsibilities</strong>:</p>
<p>Duties of this internship include, but are not limited to:&nbsp;</p>
<div>
<ul>
<li>Support a teacher(s) in an assigned class utilizing course of study adopted by The Einstein Academy, and other appropriate learning activities.</li>
</ul>
<ul>
<li>Provide individualized and small group instruction in order to adapt the curriculum to the needs of assigned student(s).</li>
</ul>
<ul>
<li>Work with assigned students who need additional support on subjects such as Language Arts, Math, Science, History, and Social Studies.</li>
</ul>
<ul>
<li>Work with assigned teacher on lesson plans and instructional materials.</li>
</ul>
<ul>
<li>Work with assigned teacher to maintain standards of student behavior needed to achieve a functional learning atmosphere in the classroom.&nbsp;</li>
</ul>
<ul>
<li>Support a teacher in identifying student needs and help students support students who need help with social and learning problems.</li>
</ul>
</div></div>
			</div>
			</div><div class="et_pb_column et_pb_column_1_2 et_pb_column_5  et_pb_css_mix_blend_mode_passthrough et-last-child">
				
				
				<div class="et_pb_module et_pb_text et_pb_text_2  et_pb_text_align_left et_pb_bg_layout_light">
				
				
				<div class="et_pb_text_inner"><p><strong>Qualifications:</strong></p>
<ol>
<li>Currently enrolled at an accredited College or University</li>
<li>Interested in a teaching certificate or Associate degree</li>
<li>Early childhood, Social Science, Psychology students are welcome</li>
</ol></div>
